main event: A sighting of an unidentified aerial phenomenon was reported in Manchester, Pennsylvania, on June 30, 1967, suggesting possible aircraft activity.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 30 seconds., The observer described the object as exhibiting varied courses., There was uncertainty regarding the nature of the observed object, potentially being an aircraft., The report determined there was no data presented to indicate the object wasn't an aircraft., The observation included sketches and diagrams which represented the sighting.
